article.description: — Charlie Moore had 21 points as DePaul beat Marquette 68-61 on Saturday.
article.headline: Moore scores 21 to carry DePaul over Marquette 68-61
article.linkText: Moore scores 21 to carry DePaul over Marquette 68-61
article.story: MILWAUKEE -- — Charlie Moore had 21 points as DePaul beat Marquette 68-61 on Saturday. Moore hit all 10 of his free throws. Javon Freeman-Liberty had 19 points and six rebounds for DePaul (3-5, 1-5 Big East Conference). Darious Hall added seven rebounds. Nick Ongenda had five blocks. D.J. Carton scored a career-high 23 points for the Golden Eagles (8-7, 4-5). Justin Lewis added eight rebounds. Theo John had eight rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
